Created attachment 4449 Snapshot of issue
I just found the Annotation is not showing special characters if the author having special characters in the name. Its fine in History but improper only in Annotation section as far as I can see. A quick search in bug db returned nothing hence filing a new.
A snapshot is attached to show the exact details. In my case, user having swedish characters in name.

I created a Mercurial repository with Swedish and other special characters in the user names, and the annotation showed up correctly in the webapp. What type of repository are you using? What's your locale?

(In reply to comment #1) > I created a Mercurial repository with Swedish and other special characters in > the user names, and the annotation showed up correctly in the webapp. What type > of repository are you using? What's your locale?
I am using GIT and locale gave me below output.
$ locale LANG=en_US.UTF-8 LC_CTYPE="en_US.UTF-8" LC_NUMERIC="en_US.UTF-8" LC_TIME="en_US.UTF-8" LC_COLLATE="en_US.UTF-8" LC_MONETARY="en_US.UTF-8" LC_MESSAGES="en_US.UTF-8" LC_PAPER="en_US.UTF-8" LC_NAME="en_US.UTF-8" LC_ADDRESS="en_US.UTF-8" LC_TELEPHONE="en_US.UTF-8" LC_MEASUREMENT="en_US.UTF-8" LC_IDENTIFICATION="en_US.UTF-8" LC_ALL= $ Please let me know if you need anymore input

Thanks!
Is the servlet container (Tomcat?) also using that locale?
I am able to reproduce the bug with a Git repository if I run the servlet container in an ISO-8859-1 locale. It looks like "git blame" always encodes its output in UTF-8 (unless overridden in .git/config), whereas OpenGrok expects the output to be encoded in the default encoding of the current locale. Because of this, OpenGrok misinterprets the encoding of non-ASCII characters. If this is the problem, you can work around it by changing the locale of the servlet container to UTF-8.

I've checked in a fix that makes OpenGrok read the log output using UTF-8 regardless of the default locale.
changeset: 1161:5310c6f819ca
Please check if this solves your problem. Thanks.

(In reply to comment #4) > I've checked in a fix that makes OpenGrok read the log output using UTF-8 > regardless of the default locale. > changeset: 1161:5310c6f819ca > Please check if this solves your problem. Thanks.

http://src.opensolaris.org/source/search?q=&project=opengrok&defs=&refs=&path=&hist=5310c6f819ca not shown anything yet.
I will give a try when I have your patch.

Created attachment 4450 patch
It looks like the changes have been reflected on src.opensolaris.org now, but I'm attaching the patch here for convenience.
There's usually a delay before src.opensolaris.org is updated, but the latest sources can always be fetched directly from the Mercurial repository:
hg clone ssh://anon@hg.opensolaris.org/hg/opengrok/trunk

Is there anything else I should do than changing the jar for indexing?
